comments: Hardaway Jr. (DAL) extends both hands into Schroder (LAL) and dislodges him from his position.
Brown Jr. (LAL) establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wood (DAL) jumps vertically contesting the drive to the basket by Gabriel (LAL).
Gabriel (LAL) leads with his knee and delivers contact to Wood's (DAL) midsection that dislodges him from his legally obtained defensive position at the end of the drive.
Schroder (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Hardaway Jr. (DAL) prior to incidental contact occurring at the start of the drive.
Westbrook (LAL) initiates contact with Doncic (DAL) off ball and affects his FOM.
At the end of the drive, Gabriel (LAL) initiates contact with Wood (DAL) as he attempts to pass.
Wood (DAL) places a hand on Westbrook (LAL) and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) jumps towards James (LAL) near the basket and the body contact is marginal.

Bullock (DAL) dislodges the ball from James (LAL) before he returns to the floor and a held ball should not have been whistled. When play resumes with a jump ball, the jumper for Dallas should have been Bullock instead of Dinwiddie (DAL).
Gabriel (LAL) closes out to the side of Hardaway Jr. (DAL) during the jump shot attempt and any contact as he returns to the floor is marginal.
Doncic (DAL) commits a take foul on James (LAL).
Doncic (LAL) releases the throw-in within five seconds.

Replay review of the foul called on Bullock (DAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Bullock (DAL) commits a take foul, but the foul is committed on Westbrook (LAL) and not Schroder (LAL).
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) legally contests Brown Jr.'s (LAL) jump shot attempt and makes contact with the ball. Any "high-five" contact is considered incidental.
Gabriel (LAL) jumps alongside Dinwiddie (DAL) and marginal body contact occurs during Dinwiddie's dunk attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) is late to the spot and does not establish himself in a legal guarding position prior to contact occurring with Gabriel (LAL) during the play at the basket.
James (LAL) brings his off-arm slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) as James releases away during the drive.
Dinwiddie (DAL) initiates contact with James (LAL) in the lane that causes him to trip, affecting his SQBR.
Doncic (DAL) brings his off-arm slightly toward Brown Jr. (LAL) and marginal contact occurs as Doncic releases away during the drive.

As Hardaway Jr. (DAL) goes underneath the pick, him and Gabriel (LAL) engage and are moving in the same direction. Gabriel does not extend into Hardaway Jr.'s path or otherwise dislodge him from his position.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) firms up on his right foot in Westbrook's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Brown Jr. (LAL) establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wood (DAL) initiates contact to James' (LAL) left arm before blocking the shot, and the illegal contact affects his shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) initiates contact to Gabriel's (LAL) arm, which affects his ability to control the rebound.
Gabriel (LAL) moves alongside Dinwiddie's (DAL) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
James (LAL) extends his hands into Dinwiddie (DAL) during the pick to create space as he rolls.
James (LAL) posts up in the lane with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and the marginal contact does not dislodge Hardaway Jr. from his defensive position.
James (LAL) extends his left arm and initiates contact with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) as the pass is made, subsequently affecting Hardaway Jr.'s ability to defend it.
Wood (DAL) cleanly blocks James' (LAL) shot attempt at the rim.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) does not deliver illegal contact to Schroder (LAL) as both players move up court at the start of the possession.
Brown Jr. (LAL) continues moving into Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and does not give him any room to avoid the contact.
Schroder (LAL) contests the post shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Dinwiddie's (DAL) arm after the release.
Gabriel (LAL) establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wood (DAL) dislodges Gabriel (LAL) from his rebounding position, which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Gabriel (LAL) establishes himself in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Powell (DAL) briefly places a hand on Gabriel's (LAL) shoulder but immediately removes it without impacting his ability to get to the rebound.
Westbrook (LAL) commits a take foul on Hardaway Jr. (DAL).
Schroder (LAL) wraps his left arm around Bullock's (DAL) hip, affecting his SQBR.
Schroder (LAL) briefly engages and disengages with Powell (DAL) as he goes underneath the screen.
